oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cabinet card showing the Dickey home in Lincoln County
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This cabinet card photograph shows the home of John Marshall Dickey, shown as number 1 in the image. Dickey was a veteran of Co. A, 44th Tenn. Inf. Regt, CSA. He was detailed as a blacksmith until captured at Chickamauga (Geo.) on September 18, 1863. He was held as a prisoner of war at Rock Island until released in May 1865. The Dickey family lived near Kelso, Lincoln County (Tenn."
